Coffees made with camel milk have gone on sale at a UK coffee shop for the first time today.

Leading coffee house Taylor Street Baristas is selling the camel milk coffees at its store in Bank, central London and they will also be served at its Brighton store on Saturday.

Customers were asked to make a suggested donation of £1 above the standard price of the coffee and all the money raised will go towards the agricultural development charity Farm Africa.

Camel milk, which has a 'clean and palatable' taste similar to semi-skimmed cow's milk, is rich in fatty acids and has around half the fat of cow's milk as well as up to three times the amount of vitamin C. It is also rich in unsaturated fatty acids.

