The idea was dreamed up by Richard Ford, deputy fresh foods editor at trade magazine The Grocer who is raising funds for Farm Africa by running the Brighton Half Marathon on 16 February.

Camel milk It is used in coffees sold throughout the UAE and has been imported into the EU by Emirates Industry for Camel Milk & Products since July last year under the brand name Camelicious.

A number of stalls at farmers markets have sold coffees using camel milk, but this is thought to be the first time a major supplier has sold camel milk drinks.

